text: Kim Min-sun (born 16 June 1999) is a South Korean speed skater. She won gold in the women's 500 metres event at the 2016 Winter Youth Olympics in Lillehammer and competed in the women's 500 metres at the 2018 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female speed skaters Category:Olympic speed skaters of South Korea Category:Speed skaters at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Speed skaters at the 2017 Asian Winter Games Category:Competitors at the 2016 Winter Youth Olympics Category:Youth Olympic gold medalists for South Korea
